---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="How It Works · AroraMSP"
  description="Four clear stages from first conversation to final handover. Fixed fees, no surprises, and documentation you own at the end."
  page="process"
  canonical="https://aroramsp.com/process"
  ogTitle="How It Works - AroraMSP"
  ogDescription="Four clear stages from first conversation to final handover. Fixed fees, no surprises, and documentation you own at the end."
>
  <section class="page wrap">
    <div class="page-head">
      <div class="sec-label">Process</div>
      <h2>A clear process, from first conversation to final handover.</h2>
      <p>No ambiguity about what happens next, what it costs, or what you will receive. Four stages with fixed fees and documentation you own at the end, written to be maintained by your internal team or any future IT provider.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-controls-wrap">
      <div class="faq-controls">
        <button class="btn-icon tip-left" id="stepsExpandAll" data-tip="Expand all" aria-label="Expand all">+</button>
        <button class="btn-icon tip-right" id="stepsCollapseAll" data-tip="Collapse all" aria-label="Collapse all">−</button>
      </div>
      <div class="process-steps" id="steps">
      <div class="step reveal reveal-delay-1" data-step="1" aria-expanded="true">
        <div class="step-head">
          <span class="step-num">01</span>
          <h4>Discovery call</h4>
          <span class="chev">›</span>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          A 30-minute call at no charge. I ask where it hurts, you tell me what you have tried and what has not worked. No sales pitch, no slide deck. I will give you an honest assessment of whether your situation is something I can solve and what that would look like. If I am not the right fit, I will say so and point you toward someone who is. You will know within 30 minutes whether this engagement makes sense and what the next step costs.
          <span class="dur">30 min · free · no obligation</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step reveal reveal-delay-2" data-step="2" aria-expanded="false">
        <div class="step-head">
          <span class="step-num">02</span>
          <h4>Tenant audit</h4>
          <span class="chev">›</span>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          Read-only access to your tenant. I run a full audit covering security posture, identity and Conditional Access configuration, license utilization by user, mail flow and DNS health, and admin role assignments. You receive a findings document in plain English covering what is working, what is broken, and what is at risk. Every item is prioritized by business impact, not technical complexity. This document is yours to keep regardless of whether you engage further.
          <span class="dur">3 to 5 business days · fixed fee</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step reveal reveal-delay-3" data-step="3" aria-expanded="false">
        <div class="step-head">
          <span class="step-num">03</span>
          <h4>Scoped plan</h4>
          <span class="chev">›</span>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          Based on the audit findings, you receive a written scope document with line-item fixed prices. Every item has an effort estimate, a clear description of what will be done, and a fixed cost. You decide what moves forward and what can wait. Nothing proceeds without your written approval. No open-ended billing, no scope creep, no invoices for work you did not explicitly approve.
          <span class="dur">1 to 2 days · included after audit</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step reveal reveal-delay-4" data-step="4" aria-expanded="false">
        <div class="step-head">
          <span class="step-num">04</span>
          <h4>Execution and handover</h4>
          <span class="chev">›</span>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          I do the work against the agreed scope. You receive a weekly status note and a live change log throughout. All configuration is documented and stored in your SharePoint or a repository you own. A final handover call walks your team through what changed, why, and how to maintain it. Nothing lives in my systems when the project closes. Your environment is fully documented and your team can maintain it without coming back to me.
          <span class="dur">1 to 3 weeks · scope-dependent</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script>
    document.querySelectorAll('.step').forEach((step) => {
      step.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const isOpen = step.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';
        step.setAttribute('aria-expanded', isOpen ? 'false' : 'true');
      });
    });
    document.getElementById('stepsExpandAll')?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      document.querySelectorAll('.step').forEach((s) => s.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true'));
    });
    document.getElementById('stepsCollapseAll')?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      document.querySelectorAll('.step').forEach((s) => s.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false'));
    });
  </script>
</Layout>
